			      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
				        <ab>Success! In the estate of Ukhasiri, the notable (<foreign xml:lang="pra-Latm">gahapati</foreign>) Budhisiri, son of Dhaṁmavāniya, resident of Kaṁṭakasala, caused to be made this stone
						<foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">maṇḍapa</foreign>, together
					with a <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">gandhakuṭī</foreign>, a
					railing (<foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">vedikā</foreign>), and
					a portal (<foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">toraṇa</foreign>).</ab>
			      </div>
			      <!--<div type="commentary"></div>-->
			      <div type="bibliography">
				        <p>First edited and described by <bibl>
						            <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Vogelc"/>:
							<citedRange>(A)</citedRange>
					          </bibl> and then by <bibl>
						            <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Venkataramanayya1974b"/>:
							<citedRange>(A)</citedRange>
					          </bibl>. His publication, which does not mention Vogel’s,
					seems nevertheless to be directly based on it for readings
					and perhaps also for the estampages. Re-edited here from
					published documentation and after autopsy of the stone.</p>
